@deftp Class <clutter-model>
Derives from @code{<gobject>}.

This class defines no direct slots.

@end deftp

@defop Signal <clutter-model> row-added  (arg0@tie{}@code{<clutter-model-iter>})
The ::row-added signal is emitted when a new row has been added. The data on the
row has already been set when the ::row-added signal has been emitted.

Since 0.6

@end defop

@defop Signal <clutter-model> row-removed  (arg0@tie{}@code{<clutter-model-iter>})
The ::row-removed signal is emitted when a row has been removed. The data on the
row pointed by the passed iterator is still valid when the ::row-removed signal
has been emitted.

Since 0.6

@end defop

@defop Signal <clutter-model> row-changed  (arg0@tie{}@code{<clutter-model-iter>})
The ::row-removed signal is emitted when a row has been changed. The data on the
row has already been updated when the ::row-changed signal has been emitted.

Since 0.6

@end defop

@defop Signal <clutter-model> sort-changed 
The ::sort-changed signal is emitted after the model has been sorted

Since 0.6

@end defop

@defop Signal <clutter-model> filter-changed 
The ::filter-changed signal is emitted when a new filter has been applied

Since 0.6

@end defop


